  <li id="comment-44616" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Melanie G</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2014/06/right-now/#comment-44616"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2015-12-24T08:21:43-05:00">Thursday, December 24, 2015 at 8:21 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#8217;m new here and have been reading through your archived posts. I have a 10 month old who is just exploring and expanding her food world, and I&#8217;ve loved reading about your food philosophy with June! </p>
<p>I made this recipe earlier this week and it was a huge hit for all of us. I make our sandwich bread and regularly pulvarize a piece at the end of the loaf for breadcrumbs, and add them to a jar in the freezer. So I used 3oz if those instead of straight up bread and it worked really well. I realized while we were eating the meatballs that there must have been a bit of whole wheat rye bread in the mix &#8211; it added a different and lovely dimension! </p>
<p>I&#8217;ll definitely be making this again. Thanks for sharing your life with us!</p>
         
  
